Present location: INSTITUT DE PAPYROLOGIE ET D'ÉGYPTOLOGIE, UNIVERSITÉ DE LILLE III [02/049] LILLE
Technique: WRITTEN WITH A REED PEN/REED WITH SPLIT NIB
Name: Literary papyrus
Description: Traces of five lines of text are preserved on this literary papyrus. The preserved letters are clearly legible, but the proposed syllables do not allow for the reconstruction of the meaning of the text.
